                        "displayName": "Christoph Roensch",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "While the ->find*() functions are syntactic Sugar they not provide any namespacing or aliasing. Therefor it's pretty useless in bigger Projects.\r\n\r\nI usually create Table and Row Classes and write simple proxy functions in the Row Class.\r\n{code:title=QuestionRow}\r\n\/**\r\n * @return SectionRow\r\n *\/\r\npublic function getSection()\r\n{\r\n  return $this->findParentRow('namespace_SectionTable');\r\n}\r\n{code}\r\nWorkaround indeed.",
